description: Issue #136
name: potenza del pensiero

description: Many years after a devastating war that killed 80% of the population, Earth is now being watched by a group of beings known as The Third, named for the third red eye on their forehead that can access various computer systems. Navigating this barren, apocalyptic landscape is Honoka, a jill-of-all-trades who uses her powerful third blue eye to detect life forces in battle as she attempts to keep her friends from The Third's deadly grasp. The prequel to the action-packed anime takes us to a time before Hanoka is known as the formidable but graceful Sword Dancer, to the beginning of her quest to save the world, to a time when she scarcely understands the powers with which she has been blessed...
name: Vol. 1

description: Surrounded by shifting sands, Honoka begins uncovering the true nature of her future as well as the past that has led her there. Meeting with things that have shaped the Dune Runner she will one day become--the scarred and shadowed Dune senior, Lidell, and the deadly soldier virus--Honoka comes ever closer to her future as savior and Sword Dancer in this second volume of The Third: Apprentice Girl on a Dessert Planet.
name: Vol. 2

description: In a future filled with a boundless potential for interstellar peace and prosperity, Mikako joins a research team to explore the recent contact between humans and alien races. She ventures out into space, leaving behind Noboru, the one young man she loves. As she travels deeper into this new frontier, her only connection with her boyfriend is through cell-phone text messages. But the years pass, and Mikako barely ages in the timelessness of space--while Noboru grows older and considers moving on with his life...
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: Voices of a Distant Star: Hoshi no Koe

description: Issue #211
name: Bianca e i sette troll

description: In the past, the devil R received his invincible powers from "The Book of S&M." But one day, an unknowing youth stole "The Book of S&M," cut it up into bits, and created a girl doll called "S" and a boy doll called "M" out of papier mache. The power that the devil held from "The Book of S&M" was now divided between 2 dolls.
name: Vol. 1

description: In 1431, France's General Gilles de Rais was Joan of Arc's dear friend who failed to rescue her before she was burned at the stake. This could explain why de Rais suddenly becomes obsessed with Sekai when she and Sovieul find themselves in his castle...though it doesn't explain why de Rais believes Sekai is Joan of Arc! Of course, with Machiavello lurking in the background, deceit and deviltry should absolutely be expected! Machiavello escapes through time, telling Sekai to take care of her body (which houses the gem he wants) until he returns for it again. Sekai, Sovieul and the doll S are reunited and prepare to jump through time again.
name: Vol. 2

description: Issue #208
name: l'isola dei misteri

description: Moon Bin Kim dreams of living in a different time--a time in which homework doesn't exist, and what is best in life is living by a warrior's ethic. However, this 20th-century student should be careful what he wishes for...he suddenly must come to terms with why he constantly finds himself living life in the 13th century as the son of a prominent warrior family! Are his dreams becoming reality--or is reality just a waking nightmare?
name: Vol. 1

description: Issue #209
name: il signore della montague

description: The Mongol princess Ah-Than-Ha-Das, determined to prove that a sword alone doesn't make the warrior, disguises as a man in order to enter a competition. When the forces of Koryo attack her, she stumbles across the familiar face of Sa-Kyung. But what will he do to this woman who is attacking his country?
name: Vol. 2

description: As the Mongolian Army threatens the prestigious Koryo army, Sa-Le-Ta-Yi, prince and general of the Mongolian Army, has given Koryo an ultimatum: Serve under the Mongolian Army or go to war! When the general of Koryo refuses, that means one thing--a brutal war filled with bloodshed and death will rage between the two territories.
name: Vol. 3

description: All Moon Bin Kim ever wanted in life was a caring mother he could love. Finally, in his 13th-century existence, his dream is fulfilled--but this outsider from the 20th-century should be careful what he wishes for. Can Moon Bin protect the most important person in his new life, or will he once again be without someone to love?
name: Vol. 4

description: Kim Moon-Bin mourns the loss of his mother, but there is little time for grieving since the war has escalated. In the midst of the chaos and confusion, he decides to go to Ghu-Zhu Castle to see his father and along the way he ponders over the words his sister spoke in a vision... "revenge."
name: Vol. 5

description: Upon receiving the package of his wife's severed head from the Mongols, Kim Kyung-Sohn burns the box. When the troops at Ghu-Zhu Palace get word of the Mongol troops approaching, Kim Kyung-Sohn decides to take matters into his own hands and face the troops...all alone. Sali Tayi is stunned by Kim Kyung-Sohn's lone presence. The strength of his presence, though, is not merely that of any ordinary man--he fights like an army of thousands!
name: Vol. 6

description: Flung into a Mongol military slave camp, Moon-Bin endures arduous combat training in order to be part of a Shield Unit, human fodder for enemy arrows. Orphaned, alone and now forced to fight for his oppressors, Moon-Bin descends into savagery, embracing the only philosophy he knows to be true: Kill or be killed. He becomes an animal in war, a feral beast driven only by the compulsion to survive. His brutality catches the eye of a Mongol general, who believes he can mold this enraged youth into a valuable military commander...
name: Vol. 7

description: Winning notice in the upper ranks of the Mongol Army, the slave Moon-Bin--or rather the son of the great General Kim Kyung-Sohn in the reality that Moon-Bin now finds himself--may once again be reunited with the beautiful and compassionate Atan Hadas, who has becoming increasingly disgusted with the decadence and carelessness of the Mongol high command. But Moon-Bin might also soon come to the attention of General Sali Tayi, a man who has sworn to destroy the Kyung-Sohn family!
name: Vol. 8

description: Having been promoted in the field of battle, Moon-Bin now realizes he cant battle his own countrymen and deserts the Mongol army, only to be caught by Sali Tayi. But the fluid of time begins pulling him again toward his own era before he is able to avenge his 13th-century family, begging questions of where in time his heart truly belongs. Especially as his affection for Atan Hadas only continues to grow amid bloodshed and tears.
name: Vol. 9

description: Once again in the command of men, civilian militiamen as they are, Moon-Bin demonstrates deft leadership in driving away Mongol soldiers. However, his popularity is growing and one of the fleeing soldiers recognizes him. It isn't long before Sali Tayi hears of the re-emergence of the man who has now become his most hated foe. And that hatred may doom any man who decides to follow the young, lonely, time-traveling hero.
name: Vol. 10

description: Upon being flooded with all of Sali Tayi's memories, Kim Moon Bin comes to the striking conclusion that he was once Sali Tayi. This revelation leads him to seek out Sali Tayi and engage in what will become their final confrontation. But will it be the young Sali, or the old Sali that emerges victorious? Read on as Threads of Time comes full circle with a spectacular meeting between the past and the present!
name: Vol. 11

description: The Igura: a deadly battle game where players stake their lives in the ruined city of Toshima. In a post-apocalyptic Japan where the underworld rules the day, Akira is placed in jail for murder. He's given a chance at freedom if he can win the game. Whether he finds victory, death, or even love, he will be in for the fight of his life! Based on the ground-breaking bishonen game!
name: Vol. 1

description: In the dark world of the Igura, only one figure strikes terror into the souls of the men who risk their lives for fame and glory. His name is Shiki and death awaits those who meet his blade. Can Akira fight off the mysterious swordsman and win back his own freedom? Or will he be saved by an unlikely friend?!
name: Vol. 2

description: Akira and Rin have their doubts about Keisuke's preparedness for the Igura, doubts shared by Keisuke himself after witnessing the horrific aftermath of Takeru's insane killing spree. But when he sees massacred bodies strewn all over, will he be able to endure the brutality that is the lawless Igura? And while old mysteries have yet to be solved, new ones continue to arise. Where did the mysterious 50% pure line come from? And what of Akira's past?
name: Vol. 3

description: Developments in the murky world of Toshima escalate as the participants of Igura obsessively seek out the addictive 50% Pure Line. What path will Akira take after witnessing the grotesque aftermath of a bloody massacre while constantly being hunted by Takeru who is more savagely deluded and intoxicated with each encounter? And what twisted lengths will disheartened Keisuke go in order to prove himself to Akira? As old mysteries unravel, is becomes apparent there is no hope for change, much less survival.
name: Vol. 4

description: After a fierce fight with the crazed Takeru, a confused and exhausted Akira wanders the streets. What causes the Line compatibility disorders, and how might they be related to his blood? And what clandestine knowledge of Nicole Premiere's terrifying power does Shiki have locked in his memories? As these weighty questions loom ever larger and the brutal Igura battles intensify, Akira is suddenly abducted by a Line-addled Keisuke, who reveals a horrifying secret of his own even as he tortures his one-time friend...
name: Vol. 5

description: Bloodied and broken by countless fights, Akira escapes from the captivity enforced by his Line-crazed best friend-turned-torturer Keisuke only to be imprisoned again--this time in Toshima's castle! There, as a token of goodwill, Toshima's perverse head honcho offers Akira some very unwelcome information about Akira and Keisuke's past, which reveals the secret behind Akira's relationship with Line! But it seems another ghost from the past will stop at nothing to access Akira's special abilities...
name: Vol. 6

description: Ranmaru Shindo joined the Special Riot Squad to avenge the mysterious death of his parents five years ago--a crime that has gone unsolved. Recently, he has been having recurring dreams of a young woman covered in blood, wielding a giant sword. And when this mysterious woman suddenly appears in front of him as a member of the Special Public Safety Task Force (TOKKO), Ranmaru's dreams suddenly become frightening real... A violent earthquakes hit Tokyo and rumors of a demon-like creature unleashing its superhuman powers upon the city--forcing Ranmaru to begin a journey to uncover the true nature of TOKKO and its strange and sundry members.
name: Devil's Awaken

description: Ranmaru Shindo discovers that he has already met Sakura Rokujo, the mysterious young woman from TOKKO--is this connection the reason that the monsters are attacking them? And when Shindo realizes that he needs protect his sister, his only remaining family, he will have to tap into a dark power that lies within him, even if doing so means risking his very life!
name: Devil's Awaken

description: More survivors of the Machida incident are found, but are they friend or foe? As Itto continues his quest for revenge, the boys face their greatest challenge yet...
name: Phantom Hunter

description: The cats are back! With Mew Ichigo studying abroad in London, the remaining four girls from Cafe Mew Mew are one too few. Luckily, a new Mew is about to emerge. Berry just transferred to a different junior high because she thought their school outfits were cute. Little does she know she's about to become the first Mew Mew with TWO sets of animal genes in her blood. Half cat, half rabbit, she's joining the Mew Mew team just in time: A new gang calling itself the Crusaders has appeared, and its leader just happens to love wild game like rabbit--well done and served for his dinner! When Mew Ichigo returns from London she's going to be very, very surprised!!!
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: Tokyo Mew Mew a la Mode

description:
The girls from Mew Mew are back with a vengeance. But this time they're up against their worst enemy ever--their fans!!! Someone is slipping secret subliminal messages about the Mews into television shows, the Internet and more. With not-so-friendly statements like "Down with the Mew Mew," and "Hate the Mews!" slipping into the media, everyone who watches TV is about to go into a trance where they hate anything and everything Mew! Even Mew Berry's crush buys into the Mew Mew hating frenzy. What in the world is a Mew to do?

Contents

  • Tokyo Mew Mew a la Mode
  • Petite Mew Mew
  • Rabbit Starfall
name: Vol. 2

volume.name: Tokyo Mew Mew a la Mode

description: Issue #139
name: passioni segrete

description: Some new players on the scene means that the struggle for the streets is getting even more personal. And now the Grand Bishop gets his hands dirty by offering Big Bubba the services of a bad mofo named Jyada. Jyada hits the Hands. The Hands hit Bubba. Bubba hits the Hands. And this whole play leads to Mera and Iwao gearing up for some swordplay.
name: Vol. 5

description: Everybody's caught in a nightmare: Iwao is haunted by visions of the beast Jyada. Steno is wracked with guilt over his new mission. Mera's standing in the jaws of a man whose son he killed. Chef's at the mercy of some ugly thugs in a dark alley. And Sunmi has to see Skunk naked. Yep--all hell's bustin' loose. But when Saru strikes back, everybody better be ready to party.
name: Vol. 6

description: From acclaimed artist Hee Jung Park, creator of Hotel Africa and Fever, comes ten stories of love, sadness, longing and alienation, all rendered in a hauntingly beautiful style. In these mesmerizing tales, a young man finds himself continuously drawn into the orbit of future suicide victims, while another finds redemption in an unlikely ally. And an apathetic lover can only enliven his pallid relationship with the crimson color of blood...
name: Vol. 1

name: Odyssey, Part 6: The Huntsman

description:
Brought to Light is an Original Graphic Novel anthology to exposure 30 years of shady deals the American Government has been up to. The choice of name on the anthology is a play on the saying to "bring something to light", meaning to make it visible.

Story Lists:

Shadowplay: The Secret Team

By Alan Moore and Bill Sienkiewicz

This is a satiric tale of the "Secret Team" the Reagan admission commissioned in Nicaragua

(Middle story)

Ailing Constitution

By Paul Mavrides

Flashpoint: The La Penca Bombing

By Joyce Brabner and Thomas Yeates

This is a journalistic style tale of the CIA's pivotal attempt to assassinate independent Nicaraguan contra leader Eden Pastora in a bombing at La Penca.
name: Brought to Light

volume.name: Brought to Light: Thirty Years of Drug Smuggling, Arms Deals, and Covert Action

In this final STARMAN OMNIBUS hardcover featuring issues #61-81 of the classic series, Jack Knight's worst nightmare becomesreality, asOpal City burns to the ground and chaos ensues, with hundreds of villains seizing the chance to strike.

Then, after a meeting with Superman and a last talk with his brother David, Jack must uncover the mystery of the Starman of 1951 by going back in time to meet him face to- face!

description: Bruised and battered after his run-in with the Green Folk, Roland is left to recover in the care of the Sisters of Eluria. He continues his strange journey in a place shrouded in ominous mysteryand discovers that the nuns may be brewing far more dangerous plans than he imagined.
name: Issue 2 (of 5)

volume.name: The Dark Tower: The Gunslinger - The Little Sisters of Eluria

description: The cant-miss last issue of the celebrated prequel to the Eisner-nominated series DO ANDROIDS DREAM OF ELECTRIC SHEEP?! Can Charlie Victor and Malcolm Reed put an end to the renegade androids? Find out as Chris Roberson (I, ZOMBIE) closes another chapter of Philip K. Dicks classic sci-fi world that inspired BLADE RUNNER!

volume.name: Do Androids Dream of Electric Sheep? Dust to Dust

description: Blood runs in the streets of Rome as mortal and vampyre clash. Resurrected by the blood of the Dracul, Caesar's ultimate ambition is finally at hand. Valens is pitted against his former master as he, Brutus and Caesar meet in a 3-way battle for the future of Rome in this epic conclusion to the story of the birth of Draculus Caesar.
name: The Die Is Cast

description: 1945. The two atomic bombs dropped on Hiroshima and Nagasaki seem to have put an end to the evil plots of William of Lecce. In liberated Paris, Daniel Rosenthal, a survivor of the death camps, learns how to live again. He owes his survival to a 'star,' a strange tarot card given to him by the surrealist poet Robert Desnos in the Terezn concentration camp, who also told him about the mysterious cabaret, L'Arcane 17. Daniel begins a descent into a world he did not know existed and into a story that the textbooks do not teach: the secret history.
name: Book Fourteen: The Watchers

description: Based on the all-new animated series! Join CLIFFJUMPER and ARCEE as they battle their way through DECEPTICON forces in a desperate adventure to learn the secrets of Space Bridge Technology! STARSCREAM, the DECEPTICON enforcer stands in their way, not just from the mission, but to rejoin OPTIMUS PRIME and his AUTOBOTS as well! This is the PREQUEL to the new hit TV Show!

Young Vimal is an outcast, constantly bullied and brutalized by his peers. Having never met his father, he has been told by his schoolmates that he's the horrific offspring of a demon that impregnated his noble mother. When he accidentally awakens Jara, an actual demon of sinister beauty and malevolent power, from a centuries-long slumber, his life takes a turn for the evil. Fed by the boy's anger and pain, Jara twists the trauma into a thirst for vengeance, offering him a 'magic' powder with which to exact revenge on his tormentors. But such gifts come with a price...This original tale is the first East-meets-West collaboration between British comics' master Mike Carey (X-Men, Lucifer, Unwritten) and Indian writer Samit Basu (Devi, Tall Tales).
name: One-Shot

description: Dr. Chaos comes to town just in time to destroy Monument Point before the Justice Society of America can completely rebuild it. Plus, Blue Devil pitches in!
name: Supertown, Part Four

description: The last place Lex Luthor expected his quest for the Black Lantern energy to take him was Arkham Asylum specifically to the cell of The Joker! What clues about Lex's quest could The Joker have to offer, and why on Earth would Lex trust him? Get ready for a one-of-a-kind confrontation between comics' two greatest villains, as brought to you by the twisted minds of Paul Cornell and Pete Woods!
name: The Black Ring, Part Eight

description: Robin and Ravager stand alone against the Feral Boys as Raven makes one last, desperate attempt to reach Headcase. Where are the rest of the Titans and who is the mysterious figure calling to them for help? Pay close attention as a lost Titan reaches out!
name: After School Special

description: "Pupaphobia" continues with Zatanna discovering a memory long repressed from her childhood on the road... the memory of the night that sadistic puppeteer Oscar Hempel tried to kill her! But while she thought her father's magic cut Hempel's strings long ago, he's back and out for vengeance and Zee may have no choice but to reverse his curse and set him free to kill again!
name: Stringleshanks; Brace Yourself

description: With Green Arrow back in full form, the gangs of Star City begin looking for their own MVPs to step forward. Are Star City and Ollie ready for Black Arrow? "The Rise of Black Arrow" begins here in this BRIGHTEST DAY tie-in!
name: Exorcising the Demons

description: Now at the mercy of the deadly Mirror House, Dick Grayson must fight for his life against one of Gotham City's oldest and most powerful evils!. Be here for the shocking conclusion to "The Black Mirror," the first arc by the highly anticipated new creative team of writer Scott Snyder and artist Jock!
name: The Black Mirror, Part Three of Three

description:
Tom and Cat have escaped Thane and the Darklords, but escaped to where?! The reality of being in an alternate reality settles in for Tom, as does the fact that he may never return home.

As Tom and Cat try to make sense of this familiar yet foreign new world, they discover new friends, new versions of people they have already met, and new dangers.

Not to mention the pursuing Darklords are close behind and are furious that their prey has eluded them thus far.
